params.smartAccount: The address of the smart account to check

params.moduleTypeId: The module type ID to check against

returns._0: true if the module is of the given type

params.data: The signature and associated data to validate
params.hash: The hash of the data that was signed
params.sender: The address that is requesting the signature validation

returns._0: magicValue Either EIP1271_SUCCESS or EIP1271_FAILED as per EIP-1271

onInstall(bytes).details: Sets up the validator configuration for the smart account

onUninstall(bytes).details: Cleans up the validator configuration for the smart account

params.bytecodeHash: The bytecode hash of the stateless validator contract
params.statelessValidator: The address of the stateless validator contract

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.details: Main validation logic that verifies keyData against the keystore state rootThe validation timeline works as follows:      - validAfter = state root timestamp (when the key was proven to exist)      - validUntil = state root timestamp + invalidation time      This creates a time window during which signatures are considered valid,      preventing both replay attacks and signature expiration.

params.userOpHash: The hash of the user operation

KEYSTORE_CACHE().notice: The address of the Keystore cache contract that manages state roots and blockhashes

accountData(address).notice: Mapping from account addresses to their installation data

isInitialized(address).notice: Checks if the module is initialized for a smart account

isModuleType(uint256).notice: Checks if the module is of a specific type

isValidSignatureWithSender(address,bytes.notice: Validates a signature according to EIP-1271

name().notice: Returns the name of the module

onInstall(bytes).notice: Called when the module is installed in a smart account

onUninstall(bytes).notice: Called when the module is uninstalled from a smart account

statelessValidators(bytes32).notice: Mapping from registered code hashes to deployed statelessValidators

updateInvalidationTime(uint48).notice: Updates the invalidation time for a smart account

validateUserOp((address,uint256,bytes,by.notice: Validates a user operation using Keystore proofs

version().notice: Returns the version of the module
